# {{name}}

A minimal ork app generated by `ork init --template minimal` (ADR-0057).

## Quick start

```bash
ork dev          # cargo build + run + watch src/ for edits
ork build        # release build + extract AppManifest to target/release/ork-manifest.json
ork inspect ./target/release/{{name}}     # print AppManifest
ork start --port 4111                     # production mode (Studio off, OTel intent on)
```

## What's here

The shell of an ork app:

- `src/main.rs` — composition root. Builds an `OrkApp`, wires the
  `AxumServer` adapter, and calls `serve()`.
- `Cargo.toml` carries `[package.metadata.ork] bin = "{{name}}"` so
  `ork dev` knows which binary to build/run.

It exposes only the auto-generated REST/SSE surface from ADR-0056
(`/healthz`, `/readyz`, `/api/manifest`, `/swagger-ui`). Add agents,
tools, and workflows to `OrkApp::builder()` to give it real behaviour.
